Virtualization Lab - TYPE 2 Virtualization using VMware or any suitable tool like VirtualBox, including Aim, Procedure, Program, Screenshot/Result placeholders.

Aim
To create a Type 2 Virtualization Unit using VMware Workstation Player or VirtualBox with the following specifications:

Minimum 2 GB RAM

10 GB storage

Install a Guest OS (preferably an open-source OS like Ubuntu)

Procedure
Tools Required:
Virtualization Software: VMware Workstation Player (free for personal use) or Oracle VirtualBox

Open-Source ISO: Ubuntu Desktop ISO or any other lightweight open-source OS (like Lubuntu, Debian, etc.)

Steps
1. Download and Install Virtualization Software
VMware Workstation Player: https://www.vmware.com/products/workstation-player.html
OR

Oracle VirtualBox: https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

2. Download Guest OS ISO
Example: Ubuntu 22.04 Desktop ISO: https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop

3. Create a New Virtual Machine
Open VMware/VirtualBox

Click on “Create a New Virtual Machine”

Choose “Installer disc image file (iso)” and browse to the Ubuntu ISO downloaded

Select Linux as the guest OS type and Ubuntu (64-bit) as version

Set hardware resources:

RAM: 2048 MB (2 GB)

Storage: 10 GB (Dynamically allocated)

Proceed and finish setup

4. Start the Virtual Machine
Power on the VM

Boot from ISO

Install Ubuntu:

Select language and region

Choose “Install Ubuntu”

Follow the installation wizard

Create a username and password

Once installed, restart the VM and remove ISO if prompted
